          "model_id": "google/gemini-2.0-flash-001",
          "raw_output": "Time. It's something we all experience, but how we *think* about time can be very different depending on where we come from. In some cultures, like in many Western countries, time is seen as a valuable resource. Being \"on time\" is important, schedules are strictly followed, and people often feel stressed about \"wasting\" time. This can be called a \"linear\" view of time.\n\nOther cultures have a more flexible approach. For example, in some Latin American countries, relationships are often considered more important than sticking to a strict schedule. Being a little late is usually acceptable. Life flows at a different pace. It's not that these cultures don't value time, but they prioritize different things, like connection and enjoying the present moment. These cultures often have a \"cyclical\" view of time, where things happen when they need to happen.",
